 another girl’s necklace), the simplicity, the serenity, all of it denoted in its own way that kindliness which K, who himself did not possess it, recognized in all of life’s phenomena, be it the smile of a bonbon in its goffered bonnet, or the echo of an old friendship divined in another’s small talk. With a frown of concentration, occasionally releasing a series of agitated groans, which would end in a grunt of vexation, the prince was busy trying to drive six tiny balls into the center 